Governor Seyi Makinde of Oyo State has approved the appointment of a new set of permanent secretaries, Inspectors-General of education, Tutors-General and Surveyor-General in the State. Makinde announced the approval on Sunday. The Governor in a statement signed by his Chief Press Secretary, Taiwo Adisa said the newly appointed officers included seven Permanent Secretaries. Adisa in the statement made available to DAILY POST on Sunday evening in Ibadan, added that the appointment of 10 Inspectors-General of Education, 10 Tutors-General and the Surveyor-General of the State have been approved by the Governor. He said that the newly appointed officers would be inaugurated soon. The Governor said that the approval followed a thorough process, which included written and oral examinations. The new Permanent Secretaries according to the statement included; Fatai Olalekan Falola, Evelyn Eseosa Akintunde, Lukman Akinola Muraina, Oluyemisi Olajumoke Adebusuyi, Modupe Elizabeth Adeleye, Tajudeen Olabode Raji and Sunday Adeyemi Ojelabi. The Governor added that Abiodun Sekore Alaba has been appointed as Surveyor-General of the State. Adebayo Olusegun Salaam, Bamidele Toyin Oyinloye, Lawrence Adelani Binuyo, Paul Oyedele Oyedokun, Lukuman Alowonle Kareem, Olarinre Alabi Adetayo Oloyede, Oyeyemi Iyabode Ojo, Olusanjo Joel Adeniyi, Faosat Ayobami Oluokun and Olajide Mamud Okesade were appointed as Inspectors-General for Education. Those who were appointed as Tutors-General according to the Governor include: Toyin Funmilola Akinyemi, Akinlolu Abiodun Akinwale, Julius Funso Folaranmi, Olatunde Lanre Suulola, Babatunde Olayinka Onifade, Haroon Animashaun Lawal, Kafari Olasunmade Babajide, Serifat Bukola Abimbola, Tunde Sakiru Adeniran and Olubukola Ajoke Oladipo.